The paper deals with the notion of wireless expansion in radio networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also involves the analysis of graph properties and algorithms, which suggests that it could be categorized under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the theoretical properties of wireless expanders and their connection to unique neighbor expanders, which could fall under information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper presents improved bounds for the spokesmen election problem, which could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves the design and analysis of algorithms.
